WEBVTT

00:00:07.360 --> 00:00:12.100
THIS IS THE STORY OF A RIVER
WHICH HAS FORMED A NATION.

00:00:12.100 --> 00:00:17.830
BUT ALSO ONE WHICH BROUGHT
IT TO THE BRINK OF DISASTER.

00:00:17.830 --> 00:00:21.330
AT OVER THREE AND A HALF
THOUSAND KILOMETERS LONG,

00:00:21.330 --> 00:00:26.930
THE MISSISSIPPI FLOWS RIGHT
THROUGH THE HEART OF AMERICA.

00:00:26.930 --> 00:00:29.030
IT HAS BROUGHT GREAT
WEALTH TO THE COUNTRY,

00:00:29.030 --> 00:00:31.330
MAKING IT THE RICHEST
NATION ON EARTH...

00:00:31.330 --> 00:00:33.860
BUT GREAT SUFFERING
AND HARDSHIP, TOO,

00:00:33.860 --> 00:00:37.900
MAKING IT IN MANY WAYS
THE MOST IMPOVERISHED.

00:00:42.100 --> 00:00:45.830
IT IS ALSO A RIVER
WHICH ROCKED A NATION.

00:00:45.830 --> 00:00:56.660
♪

00:00:56.660 --> 00:01:00.800
THE BLUES, ROCK AND ROLL, GOSPEL
AND JAZZ; THEY ALL FLOWED

00:01:00.800 --> 00:01:04.100
INTO AMERICA ON THE MUDDY
WATERS OF THE MISSISSIPPI

00:01:04.100 --> 00:01:06.330
AND OUT AGAIN TO THE
REST OF THE WORLD

00:01:06.330 --> 00:01:10.760
AS A REVOLUTION
OF SONG.

00:01:10.760 --> 00:01:13.200
STARS, SPANGLES
AND SUFFERING...

00:01:13.200 --> 00:01:17.030
THE MISSISSIPPI MADE
AMERICA WHAT IT IS TODAY.

00:01:43.460 --> 00:01:46.500
THERE'S NO PLACE IN THE
WORLD LIKE THE MISSISSIPPI.

00:01:46.500 --> 00:01:49.800
IT'S A MYSTERIOUS PLACE FULL
OF CONTRASTS AND PARADOX -

00:01:49.800 --> 00:01:54.160
NORTH, SOUTH, BLACK,
WHITE, POOR AND RICH -

00:01:54.160 --> 00:01:56.900
AND WHERE MUSIC HAS
ALWAYS BEEN PLAYED

00:01:56.900 --> 00:02:05.630
EVEN WHEN THERE WAS
VERY LITTLE TO SING ABOUT.

00:02:05.630 --> 00:02:08.660
THE STORY AND SONG OF OL'
MAN RIVER COMES THROUGH

00:02:08.660 --> 00:02:11.660
IN THE VOICES OF PEOPLE SUCH
AS DAVID "HONEYBOY" EDWARDS

00:02:11.660 --> 00:02:17.900
WHO'S THE LAST LIVING
DELTA BLUESMAN;

00:02:17.900 --> 00:02:22.330
REVEREND MILLER SMITH WHO
WORKS ALL THE HOURS GOD SENDS

00:02:22.330 --> 00:02:28.230
TO FIND SOME HOPE FOR HIS
DIRT-POOR CONGREGATION;

00:02:28.230 --> 00:02:31.960
AND ELLIS SMITH, THE OLDEST
SURVIVOR OF THE WORST FLOOD

00:02:31.960 --> 00:02:34.300
IN AMERICAN HISTORY.

00:02:34.300 --> 00:02:42.300
♪ THE OL' MAN RIVER, HE
JUST KEEPS ROLLING ALONG. ♪

00:02:42.300 --> 00:02:56.130
♪

00:02:56.130 --> 00:02:59.100
THE MISSISSIPPI BEGINS
ITS JOURNEY IN LAKE ITASCA

00:02:59.100 --> 00:03:02.100
AND RUNS SOUTH
FOR 3,700 KILOMETERS

00:03:02.100 --> 00:03:06.600
BEFORE REACHING THE
SEA IN THE GULF OF MEXICO.

00:03:06.600 --> 00:03:09.060
THIS IS A RIVER WHICH
DOMINATES THE WHOLE

00:03:09.060 --> 00:03:11.030
OF THE AMERICAN
LANDSCAPE.

00:03:11.030 --> 00:03:13.700
BUT IT'S THE SOUTHERN STRETCH,
ALSO KNOWN AS THE LOWER

00:03:13.700 --> 00:03:21.630
MISSISSIPPI, WHICH HAS DOMINATED
AMERICAN CULTURE AND LIFE.

00:03:21.630 --> 00:03:25.530
OUR STORY STARTS HERE WHERE
THE PEA GREEN FLOW OF THE OHIO

00:03:25.530 --> 00:03:30.360
MERGES WITH THE MUDDIER
WATERS OF THE MISSISSIPPI.

00:03:30.360 --> 00:03:34.160
ON THIS CONFLUENCE LIES THE
LITTLE TOWN OF CAIRO (KAY-ROO).

00:03:34.160 --> 00:03:37.230
THERE'S NO SIGNPOST OR
FRONTIER FENCE BUT THIS PLACE

00:03:37.230 --> 00:03:39.730
MARKS THE BEGINNING OF
THE LOWER MISSISSIPPI

00:03:39.730 --> 00:03:43.530
AND ALSO THE BORDER BETWEEN
AMERICA NORTH AND SOUTH.

00:03:55.330 --> 00:03:58.960
TODAY CAIRO LOOKS MORE LIKE A
FILM SET FROM AN OLD WESTERN

00:03:58.960 --> 00:04:01.600
THAN A PLACE WHERE
PEOPLE LIVE AND WORK;

00:04:01.600 --> 00:04:03.560
A MODERN DAY
GHOST TOWN.

00:04:03.560 --> 00:04:06.530
IT'S LIKE MANY OTHER PLACES
IN THE AMERICAN SOUTH WHERE

00:04:06.530 --> 00:04:12.130
POVERTY IS A KILLER DISEASE
WIPING OUT WHOLE COMMUNITIES.

00:04:12.130 --> 00:04:15.200
IN RECENT YEARS, CAIRO'S
MAINLY BLACK POPULATION

00:04:15.200 --> 00:04:19.260
HAS SHRUNK FROM 15,000
TO LESS THAN 3,000

00:04:19.260 --> 00:04:25.230
LEAVING IT A CITY OF ABANDONED
BUILDINGS AND DEAD HOPES.

00:04:25.230 --> 00:04:29.360
THERE'S NO HOSPITAL HERE,
NO PARK, NO RESTAURANT.

00:04:29.360 --> 00:04:33.160
DRUGS ARE COMMON
AND DECAY IS DOMINANT.

00:04:33.160 --> 00:04:35.730
THIS IS COMMERCIAL AVENUE WHICH
WOULD HAVE BEEN THE MAJOR

00:04:35.730 --> 00:04:38.000
COMMERCE CENTER
THROUGHOUT CAIRO'S HISTORY.

00:04:38.000 --> 00:04:40.660
IF I COULD TRAVEL BACK IN TIME
I'D LIKE TO SEE IT IN DIFFERENT

00:04:40.660 --> 00:04:42.860
DECADES LIKE THE 1880'S AND
90'S WHEN THE RIVERBOATS

00:04:42.860 --> 00:04:45.030
WERE PLYING THIS
AREA, INTO THE 30'S

00:04:45.030 --> 00:04:47.400
WHEN THE BLUES FIRST
MIGRATED NORTHWARD.

00:04:47.400 --> 00:04:49.830
IT HAD TO BE A
MAGNIFICENT MULTICULTURAL,

00:04:49.830 --> 00:04:53.330
FUN, EXCITING PLACE.

00:04:53.330 --> 00:04:57.130
>>STACE ENGLAND IS A
LOCAL MUSICIAN WHO GREW UP

00:04:57.130 --> 00:04:59.260
NOT FAR
FROM CAIRO.

00:04:59.260 --> 00:05:01.600
HE'S ALWAYS BEEN
FASCINATED WITH THIS PLACE

00:05:01.600 --> 00:05:03.630
AND HAS SPENT
MANY YEARS HERE

00:05:03.630 --> 00:05:07.860
RESEARCHING AND WRITING
SONGS ABOUT ITS RICH PAST.

00:05:07.860 --> 00:05:10.760
IT'S HARD TO BELIEVE THAT
THIS PLACE USED TO BE ONE OF

00:05:10.760 --> 00:05:14.400
THE BUSIEST AND RICHEST
PORTS IN THE COUNTRY.

00:05:14.400 --> 00:05:18.030
BUT SOMETHING HAPPENED HERE TO
MAKE CAIRO'S WEALTH DISAPPEAR

00:05:18.030 --> 00:05:20.660
IN RECENT YEARS.

00:05:20.660 --> 00:05:23.500
THIS BUILDING WAS DUKE'S
BAR WHICH OPENED IN 1933

00:05:23.500 --> 00:05:26.400
AND JUST CLOSED A COUPLE OF
YEARS AGO WHICH BROKE MY HEART.

00:05:26.400 --> 00:05:27.700
I LOVED THAT PLACE.

00:05:27.700 --> 00:05:30.600
THAT WAS MY OFFICE IN
CAIRO DURING MY RESEARCH.

00:05:30.600 --> 00:05:33.930
A BAR HERE, FATBOYS, HAS ALWAYS
BEEN A BAR FOR MANY, MANY YEARS

00:05:33.930 --> 00:05:36.330
AND CHANGED
HANDS AND NAMES.

00:05:36.330 --> 00:05:38.360
THERE WAS A VERY FAMOUS
NEON MAKER HERE IN CAIRO

00:05:38.360 --> 00:05:41.030
AND MOST OF THE SIGNS
WERE IN NEON SO IN THE 40'S

00:05:41.030 --> 00:05:43.100
YOU WOULD HAVE SEEN THIS
PLACE BLINKING AND LIGHTING UP

00:05:43.100 --> 00:05:46.530
LIKE LAS VEGAS AS
YOU WALKED AROUND.

00:05:46.530 --> 00:05:50.100
SO IT'S VERY EMOTIONAL FOR
ME TO BE IN A SPOT LIKE THIS

00:05:50.100 --> 00:05:54.260
AND HAVE A SENSE
OF THAT HISTORY.

00:05:59.960 --> 00:06:02.930
>>STACE BELIEVES THAT CAIRO
SHOULD BE CELEBRATED

00:06:02.930 --> 00:06:05.700
AND PRESERVED BECAUSE OF
THE UNIQUE ROLE IT HAS PLAYED

00:06:05.700 --> 00:06:08.930
IN AMERICAN HISTORY.

00:06:08.930 --> 00:06:13.130
IT WAS HERE IN THIS TOWN,
WHICH MARKED THE START

00:06:13.130 --> 00:06:16.100
OF THE AMERICAN NORTH, THAT
BLACK AFRICAN AMERICAN SLAVES

00:06:16.100 --> 00:06:20.530
COULD CLAIM
THEIR LIBERTY.

00:06:20.530 --> 00:06:25.160
FOR OVER 300 YEARS SLAVES WERE
SOLD TO WHITE MASTERS ALL ALONG

00:06:25.160 --> 00:06:28.200
THE MISSISSIPPI BUT THE HARSHEST
CONDITIONS WERE ALWAYS FOUND

00:06:28.200 --> 00:06:31.800
IN THE SOUTHERN STATES AND SO
MANY TRIED TO ESCAPE TO CAIRO;

00:06:31.800 --> 00:06:36.560
THEIR GATEWAY TO A
BETTER LIFE IN THE NORTH.

00:06:36.560 --> 00:06:40.060
IMAGINE YOU'RE A SLAVE IN THE
SOUTH OR RIGHT AFTER THE CIVIL

00:06:40.060 --> 00:06:42.900
WAR YOU'RE A FREED SLAVE OR A
SON OF SLAVES, CROSSING INTO

00:06:42.900 --> 00:06:46.260
THE NORTH WOULD HAVE BEEN
AN EVER CHANGING LIFE EVENT.

00:06:46.260 --> 00:06:50.530
TO FINALLY FIND YOURSELF ON FREE
SOIL AND SAY I'M A MAN NOW.

00:06:50.530 --> 00:06:53.230
NOBODY CAN TELL
ME WHAT TO DO.

00:06:53.230 --> 00:06:56.360
SO THIS WAS A DRAMATIC
POINT FOR THAT ACTIVITY.

00:06:56.360 --> 00:06:58.660
IN FACT EVEN INTO
THE 40'S IN CAIRO

00:06:58.660 --> 00:07:00.760
THIS WAS A
DEMARCATION POINT.

00:07:00.760 --> 00:07:02.800
IF YOU WERE COMING FROM
THE SOUTH ON A TRAIN CAR,

00:07:02.800 --> 00:07:04.660
YOU HAD TO RIDE IN THE
BLACK CAR BUT IN CAIRO

00:07:04.660 --> 00:07:08.000
YOU COULD SWITCH AND
RIDE IN THE MIXED RACE CAR.

00:07:08.000 --> 00:07:10.160
>>BEFORE THE DAYS
OF MODERN TRANSPORT

00:07:10.160 --> 00:07:13.430
FLEEING SLAVES TRAVELED
TO CAIRO VIA A NETWORK

00:07:13.430 --> 00:07:15.830
OF SECRET RIVER
ROUTES AND SAFE HOUSES

00:07:15.830 --> 00:07:18.930
NICKNAMED THE
"UNDERGROUND RAILROAD".

00:07:18.930 --> 00:07:22.700
THEIR JOURNEY WAS FRAUGHT WITH
DANGER AND IF THEY WERE CAUGHT

00:07:22.700 --> 00:07:25.700
THEY'D BE SOLD DOWN RIVER,
A NOTION WHICH BECAME

00:07:25.700 --> 00:07:29.560
SYNONYMOUS WITH
RECEIVING A DEATH SENTENCE.

00:07:29.560 --> 00:07:32.460
THE LUCKY ONES REACHED
CAIRO WHERE THEY WERE

00:07:32.460 --> 00:07:35.130
GREETED BY PEOPLE WHO
GAVE THEM HELP AND REFUGE

00:07:35.130 --> 00:07:38.430
AND IT IS SAID THAT ONCE
THE SLAVES ARRIVED HERE

00:07:38.430 --> 00:07:45.760
THEY FELL TO THEIR KNEES
AND KISSED THE FREE GROUND.

00:07:45.760 --> 00:07:50.600
IF YOU STAND ON THE DOCKS IN
CAIRO TODAY YOU'D BE FORGIVEN

00:07:50.600 --> 00:07:54.330
FOR THINKING THAT THE TOWN
IS STILL AS BUSY AS EVER.

00:07:54.330 --> 00:07:58.130
BUT THERE'S ONE
BIG DIFFERENCE.

00:07:58.130 --> 00:08:03.130
THESE DAYS BIGGER SHIPS
MEAN BIGGER FUEL TANKS

00:08:03.130 --> 00:08:05.260
AND FEWER
PIT STOPS.

00:08:05.260 --> 00:08:08.800
THE RESULT FOR CAIRO
HAS BEEN DEVASTATING.

00:08:08.800 --> 00:08:12.000
NOTHING STOPS
HERE ANYMORE.

00:08:18.060 --> 00:08:20.600
STACE BELIEVES THAT
NOT ALL IS LOST AND THAT

00:08:20.600 --> 00:08:23.560
IF CAIRO COULD CELEBRATE
AND CASH IN ON ITS PAST

00:08:23.560 --> 00:08:27.000
THEN MAYBE IT WOULD HAVE
SOME CHANCE OF A FUTURE.

00:08:33.730 --> 00:08:35.930
220 KILOMETERS
DOWNSTREAM

00:08:35.930 --> 00:08:42.300
THERE'S A PLACE
THAT'S DOING JUST THAT.

00:08:42.300 --> 00:08:46.860
ONCE A LITTLE TOWN SMALLER
THAN CAIRO, MEMPHIS GREW

00:08:46.860 --> 00:08:50.000
TO BECOME THE CAPITAL
OF THE MISSISSIPPI RIVER

00:08:50.000 --> 00:08:52.630
AND THE MUSIC
MECCA OF AMERICA.

00:08:52.630 --> 00:08:54.900
BLUES, SOUL, AND
ROCK AND ROLL.

00:08:54.900 --> 00:08:57.030
MEMPHIS HAS IT ALL.

00:08:57.030 --> 00:09:00.800
LOCALS CLAIM THAT ALL THIS MUSIC
ORIGINATED HERE BUT THE TRUTH IS

00:09:00.800 --> 00:09:03.400
THAT ALL THE NOTES AND
THE RIFFS AND THE RHYTHMS

00:09:03.400 --> 00:09:06.630
WERE CARRIED INTO MEMPHIS
BY THE MISSISSIPPI HERSELF;

00:09:06.630 --> 00:09:10.760
A BYPRODUCT OF ALL THE
RIVER AND SLAVE TRADES.

00:09:10.760 --> 00:09:23.060
♪

00:09:23.060 --> 00:09:27.230
MEMPHIS' GOLDEN AGE OF MUSIC
GOES BACK TO THE 1940'S, 50'S,

00:09:27.230 --> 00:09:31.360
AND 60S, WHEN MUSICIANS
LIKE ELVIS PRESLEY, BB KING

00:09:31.360 --> 00:09:34.430
AND OTIS REDDING MADE
MEMPHIS THEIR HOME

00:09:34.430 --> 00:09:37.900
AND WHEN PLACES LIKE STAX AND
SUN RECORDS GAVE STREET KIDS

00:09:37.900 --> 00:09:45.900
THE CHANCE TO BECOME
INTERNATIONAL SUPERSTARS.

00:09:45.900 --> 00:09:49.000
ITS CREATIVE HUB AT THAT
TIME WAS BEALE STREET

00:09:49.000 --> 00:09:51.700
AND TODAY IT'S ONE OF THE
LEADING TOURIST ATTRACTIONS

00:09:51.700 --> 00:09:54.100
IN THE STATE
OF TENNESSEE.

00:09:59.860 --> 00:10:02.630
BUT LONG BEFORE IT
OPENED ITS DOORS TO VISITORS,

00:10:02.630 --> 00:10:06.730
MEMPHIS WAS THE ORIGINAL
WALL STREET OF AMERICA.

00:10:12.830 --> 00:10:15.660
DURING THE 1800'S THE CITY
DEVELOPED INTO THE MOST

00:10:15.660 --> 00:10:18.630
IMPORTANT TRADING
CENTER IN THE COUNTRY.

00:10:18.630 --> 00:10:21.700
ITS STRATEGIC POSITION RIGHT
ON THE BANKS OF THE MISSISSIPPI

00:10:21.700 --> 00:10:23.660
ATTRACTED HUGE
INVESTMENT,

00:10:23.660 --> 00:10:26.330
MAKING IT THE LARGEST
COTTON CENTER IN THE WORLD

00:10:26.330 --> 00:10:31.600
AND THE LARGEST SLAVE
MARKET IN THE MID SOUTH.

00:10:31.600 --> 00:10:36.930
KING COTTON, AS IT WAS
KNOWN THEN, WAS A HUGELY

00:10:36.930 --> 00:10:41.100
PROFITABLE CASH CROP GROWN ON
THE SOUTHERN PLANTATION FARMS

00:10:41.100 --> 00:10:44.760
AND TRADED HERE.

00:10:44.760 --> 00:10:49.830
HUNDREDS OF THOUSANDS OF
PEOPLE TRAVELED TO MEMPHIS

00:10:49.830 --> 00:10:54.430
ALONG THE MISSISSIPPI
TO BUY, SELL, AND BE SOLD,

00:10:54.430 --> 00:11:00.200
FORMING WHAT WAS IN EFFECT A
HUGE MELTING POT OF CULTURES.

00:11:00.200 --> 00:11:03.800
THIS UNIQUE SHARING AND MIXING
OF BLACK AND WHITE EXPERIENCES

00:11:03.800 --> 00:11:07.660
ON THE ONE HAND SOWED THE SEEDS
FOR MEMPHIS' RICH MUSICAL LEGACY

00:11:07.660 --> 00:11:11.930
BUT ON THE OTHER CREATED A
DEEPLY ROOTED RACIAL INTOLERANCE

00:11:11.930 --> 00:11:15.060
WHICH EXPLODED DURING THE
VIOLENT CIVIL RIGHTS PROTESTS

00:11:15.060 --> 00:11:18.860
OF THE 1960'S AND 70'S.

00:11:26.160 --> 00:11:29.030
THE ASSASINATION OF MARTIN
LUTHER KING AT THE LORRAINE

00:11:29.030 --> 00:11:32.730
MOTEL IN MEMPHIS DURING THE
SPRING OF '68 IS SEEN BY MANY

00:11:32.730 --> 00:11:38.660
AS THE BEGINNING OF THE END
OF MEMPHIS' GOLDEN ERA.

00:11:38.660 --> 00:11:41.700
DURING THE LATE 60'S AND
70'S MUSICIANS STOPPED

00:11:41.700 --> 00:11:44.200
COMING TO MEMPHIS,
TRAVELING FURTHER NORTH

00:11:44.200 --> 00:11:47.630
TO PLACES LIKE CHICAGO
AND DETROIT INSTEAD.

00:11:47.630 --> 00:11:52.030
ALL THE BARS AND JUKE JOINTS ON
BEALE STREET HAD TO CLOSE DOWN,

00:11:52.030 --> 00:11:54.160
THE RECORDING STUDIOS
STOPPED RECORDING,

00:11:54.160 --> 00:11:58.460
AND THE CITY SEEMED
TO LOSE ITS HEART...

00:11:58.460 --> 00:12:03.800
BUT PERHAPS
NOT ITS SOUL.

00:12:03.800 --> 00:12:07.430
JUST A STONE'S THROW FROM THE
MISSISSIPPI IS STAX RECORDS.

00:12:07.430 --> 00:12:10.230
THIS PLACE USED TO BE ONE OF
THE LARGEST AFRICAN AMERICAN

00:12:10.230 --> 00:12:12.400
BUSINESSES IN
THE UNITED STATES

00:12:12.400 --> 00:12:16.500
AND AN OASIS OF BLACK
AND WHITE INTEGRATION.

00:12:16.500 --> 00:12:19.560
STAX WAS ALWAYS A PLACE
WHERE THE COLOR OF YOUR MUSIC

00:12:19.560 --> 00:12:25.430
WAS FAR MORE IMPORTANT
THAN THE COLOR OF YOUR SKIN.

00:12:25.430 --> 00:12:28.230
FOR THOSE OF YOU THAT
DON'T KNOW THIS LADY, SHE IS,

00:12:28.230 --> 00:12:30.360
I CONSIDER, THE
MOTHER OF STAX.

00:12:30.360 --> 00:12:35.430
LET'S GIVE A BIG HAND
TO MS. DEANIE PARKER.

00:12:35.430 --> 00:12:41.130
I WAS WITH STAX RECORDS FROM
ABOUT 1961 WHEN I CAME IN

00:12:41.130 --> 00:12:48.230
TO BE A SUPERSTAR AND I REALIZED
THAT I DIDN'T HAVE THE SOULFUL

00:12:48.230 --> 00:12:55.100
DELIVERY OF ARETHA FRANKLIN
AND I WASN'T NEARLY AS TALENTED

00:12:55.100 --> 00:12:59.730
AS GLADYS KNIGHT, AND MY
LEGS WERE NEVER GOING TO BE

00:12:59.730 --> 00:13:03.330
AS LONG AND AS GORGEOUS AS
TINA TURNER'S AND SO I DECIDED

00:13:03.330 --> 00:13:05.700
THAT I HAD TO DO SOMETHING
THAT WOULD PUT ME

00:13:05.700 --> 00:13:09.200
BEHIND THE DESK WHERE
IT REALLY DIDN'T MATTER.

00:13:09.200 --> 00:13:12.700
>>WHEN STAX WAS FORCED
INTO LIQUIDATION IN 1976,

00:13:12.700 --> 00:13:14.900
FORMER STAX SECRETARY,
DEANIE PARKER,

00:13:14.900 --> 00:13:16.800
REFUSED TO
GIVE UP HOPE.

00:13:16.800 --> 00:13:19.860
SHE GREW UP ON THE TOUGH
STREETS OF MEMPHIS AND SO KNOWS

00:13:19.860 --> 00:13:24.300
BETTER THAN MOST HOW IMPORTANT
IT IS TO HOLD ON TO THE DREAM.

00:13:24.300 --> 00:13:29.630
OVER THE PAST FEW YEARS SHE HAS
BEEN INSTRUMENTAL IN REBUILDING

00:13:29.630 --> 00:13:33.800
STAX, NOT AS A RECORDING
STUDIO BUT AS A MUSIC ACADEMY

00:13:33.800 --> 00:13:38.930
WHICH ONCE AGAIN GIVES STREET
KIDS THE CHANCE TO SHINE.

00:13:38.930 --> 00:13:44.100
IT'S UNFORTUNATE THAT FOR THE
LAST 15 YEARS CHILDREN HAVE

00:13:44.100 --> 00:13:47.230
THOUGHT THEY WERE LISTENING TO
MUSIC WHEN IN FACT THEY WEREN'T.

00:13:47.230 --> 00:13:50.960
WHAT THEY WERE LISTENING
TO WAS RHYTHM AND RHYME,

00:13:50.960 --> 00:13:54.660
ALSO KNOWN AS HIP HOP,
AND THAT GOD-AWFUL RAP.

00:13:54.660 --> 00:13:57.700
AND SO THEY'VE JUST
NOT HAD THE EXPOSURE,

00:13:57.700 --> 00:13:59.630
THEY'VE NOT HAD
THE ENCOURAGEMENT,

00:13:59.630 --> 00:14:01.700
THEY'VE NOT
HAD THE TRAINING

00:14:01.700 --> 00:14:04.960
BECAUSE WE'RE DETERMINED
TO DO FOR CHILDREN TODAY

00:14:04.960 --> 00:14:11.800
AND CHILDREN IN THE FUTURE
WHAT STAX RECORDS DID FOR US.

00:14:11.800 --> 00:14:15.700
>>BUT MUCH LIKE IT WAS IN
THE 60'S, STAX IS JUST AN OASIS

00:14:15.700 --> 00:14:19.560
WITHIN A MUCH
HARSHER ENVIRONMENT.

00:14:19.560 --> 00:14:23.600
ON THE STREETS OUTSIDE STAX,
THE AFRICAN AMERICAN COMMUNITY

00:14:23.600 --> 00:14:27.200
IS STILL STRUGGLING WITH
ENDEMIC RACISM IN A CITY

00:14:27.200 --> 00:14:32.330
WHICH IS CONSIDERED THE
MOST VIOLENT IN AMERICA.

00:14:32.330 --> 00:14:43.600
♪

00:14:43.600 --> 00:14:46.330
APART FROM ITS ROLE AS THE
SUPPORT ACT TO SOME OF THE

00:14:46.330 --> 00:14:49.360
BEST MUSIC IN THE WORLD, THE
MISSISSIPPI'S CLAIM TO FAME

00:14:49.360 --> 00:14:51.700
IS THAT IT'S THE
WORLD'S FLATTEST RIVER

00:14:51.700 --> 00:14:54.030
WHERE WATER
SKIING WAS INVENTED

00:14:54.030 --> 00:14:56.000
AND WHERE EARLY
RIVER TRADE AND TRAFFIC

00:14:56.000 --> 00:15:01.960
MADE IT THE FIRST SUPER
HIGHWAY OF THE NEW WORLD.

00:15:01.960 --> 00:15:07.260
BECAUSE IT'S SO WIDE OPEN AND
EVEN, TRAVELING UP AND DOWN

00:15:07.260 --> 00:15:10.400
THE MISSISSIPPI IS PLAIN
SAILING FOR THESE TUG BOATS

00:15:10.400 --> 00:15:13.060
WHICH CAN STRETCH UP
TO A MILE LONG AND CARRY

00:15:13.060 --> 00:15:18.130
THE SAME AMOUNT OF FREIGHT
AS A THOUSAND RAILROAD CARS.

00:15:25.360 --> 00:15:28.830
THESE ARE THE POWER HORSES OF
THE MISSISSIPPI AND THEY'RE A

00:15:28.830 --> 00:15:33.730
VERY DIFFERENT ANIMAL TO
THE ELEGANT VESSELS OF OLD.

00:15:33.730 --> 00:15:37.030
THE MISSISSIPPI PADDLE
STEAMERS ARE AS FAMOUS

00:15:37.030 --> 00:15:41.560
AS THE RIVER ITSELF, EVOKING
A NOSTALGIC SENSE OF ROMANCE

00:15:41.560 --> 00:15:44.060
AND CAREFREE ADVENTURE.

00:15:44.060 --> 00:15:47.630
ON THESE DECKS
200 YEARS AGO

00:15:47.630 --> 00:15:50.530
THERE WOULD BE A
VERY DIFFERENT CROWD.

00:15:50.530 --> 00:15:54.660
THERE'D BE SASSY WOMEN RUBBING
SKIRTS WITH CIGAR-SMOKING MEN,

00:15:54.660 --> 00:15:57.130
AND RUGGED RIVERBOAT
CAPTAINS KEEPING A LOOKOUT

00:15:57.130 --> 00:16:00.230
FOR ANY MISSISSIPPI
ROGUES OR PIRATES.

00:16:00.230 --> 00:16:02.460
ALRIGHT. SEE THAT
BIG SANDBAR THERE?

00:16:02.460 --> 00:16:05.060
QUIT LOOKING THAT WAY.

00:16:05.060 --> 00:16:10.630
THIS LADY KEEPS LOOKING
THAT WAY. QUIT IT.

00:16:10.630 --> 00:16:13.600
>>DON LANCASTER HAS
BEEN A RIVERBOAT PILOT

00:16:13.600 --> 00:16:15.630
FOR OVER 30 YEARS.

00:16:15.630 --> 00:16:18.400
AS A YOUNG MAN HE WORKED AS A
POLICE OFFICER PATROLLING THE

00:16:18.400 --> 00:16:21.200
MEAN STREETS OF MEMPHIS
BUT ALWAYS FANCIED HIMSELF

00:16:21.200 --> 00:16:25.760
AS THE ROMANTIC LEAD IN AN
EPIC RIVERBOAT ADVENTURE.

00:16:25.760 --> 00:16:29.430
I THINK I'VE LIVED MOST
OF MY LIFE ON THE RIVER.

00:16:29.430 --> 00:16:31.660
I THOROUGHLY
ENJOY IT.

00:16:31.660 --> 00:16:34.930
I DO IT SIX DAYS A WEEK,
SOMETIMES AS MANY AS

00:16:34.930 --> 00:16:39.100
FIVE TRIPS A DAY.

00:16:39.100 --> 00:16:43.130
SOME PEOPLE LIKE RACING,
SOME PEOPLE LIKE FLYING,

00:16:43.130 --> 00:16:48.930
I LOVE THE RIVER AND THAT'S
WHERE I SPEND MOST OF MY TIME.

00:16:48.930 --> 00:16:52.630
>>DON BEGAN HIS TRAINING
IN THE PARLOR HOUSES

00:16:52.630 --> 00:16:56.130
OF THE GREAT STEAMERS AND
WORKED HIS WAY UP TO CAPTAIN.

00:16:56.130 --> 00:16:58.530
HE NOW RUNS DAY TRIPS
FOR SUNDAY SAILORS

00:16:58.530 --> 00:17:00.900
WHO SEEM MORE INTERESTED
IN TAKING IT EASY

00:17:00.900 --> 00:17:04.430
THAN IN TEARING
UP THE MISSISSIPPI.

00:17:04.430 --> 00:17:07.930
AT ONE TIME MY YOUNGEST
SON WAS THE YOUNGEST PILOT

00:17:07.930 --> 00:17:09.760
ON THE MISSISSIPPI
RIVER.

00:17:09.760 --> 00:17:12.030
WE USED TO
HAVE A LOT OF FUN.

00:17:12.030 --> 00:17:14.830
WE WORKED FOR A COMPANY
THAT HAD TWO PADDLE WHEELERS

00:17:14.830 --> 00:17:18.100
AND WE'D GET OUT THERE AND
WE'D LOAD IN THE PASSENGERS

00:17:18.100 --> 00:17:20.860
AND THEN WE'D CHALLENGE
EACH OTHER TO A RACE.

00:17:20.860 --> 00:17:22.800
EVERYBODY
JUST HAD A FIT.

00:17:22.800 --> 00:17:24.500
"OH, WE'RE RACING!"

00:17:24.500 --> 00:17:26.900
AND SURE ENOUGH WE'D
GO BY DOWNTOWN MEMPHIS

00:17:26.900 --> 00:17:29.600
WIDE OPEN WITH THE
PADDLE WHEELS FLYING.

00:17:29.600 --> 00:17:31.260
I ALWAYS WON, THOUGH.

00:17:31.260 --> 00:17:34.060
YOU SEE, I TAUGHT HIM EVERYTHING
HE KNEW BUT I DIDN'T TEACH HIM

00:17:34.060 --> 00:17:38.700
EVERYTHING I KNEW AND WE
USED TO HAVE A LOT OF FUN.

00:17:43.460 --> 00:17:46.100
>>MARK TWAIN WAS
ALSO A RIVERBOAT PILOT

00:17:46.100 --> 00:17:48.830
AND ONE OF AMERICA'S
MOST FAMOUS AUTHORS.

00:17:48.830 --> 00:17:51.800
HE WROTE ABOUT THE ORIGINAL
STEAMBOAT RACES AND ABOUT

00:17:51.800 --> 00:17:55.030
ALL THE GAMBLING AND DODGY
DEALS WHICH HAPPENED HERE

00:17:55.030 --> 00:18:00.500
BEFORE GAMING WAS
OUTLAWED IN 1870.

00:18:00.500 --> 00:18:03.660
IN THE LAWLESS DAYS BEFORE
THE BIG EXPANSION INTO THE

00:18:03.660 --> 00:18:07.530
WILD WEST, THE MISSISSIPPI
WAS AMERICA'S LAST FRONTIER

00:18:07.530 --> 00:18:09.860
WITH ITS BOATS BECOMING
A POPULAR HANGOUT

00:18:09.860 --> 00:18:15.600
AND HIDEOUT FOR ALL SORTS
OF COWBOYS AND CHANCERS.

00:18:15.600 --> 00:18:18.460
IN THOSE DAYS THERE WOULD
BE MUSIC TO ACCOMPANY

00:18:18.460 --> 00:18:22.260
ALL THE ACTION AND LEGEND HAS
IT THAT JAZZ WAS INVENTED ON A

00:18:22.260 --> 00:18:25.930
MISSISSIPPI PADDLE STEAMER BY
AN ITINERANT MUSICIAN CALLED

00:18:25.930 --> 00:18:30.660
JAZBO BROWN WHO GAVE HIS
NAME TO THIS STYLE OF PLAYING.

00:18:38.260 --> 00:18:42.160
THEY SAY THAT SOME PARTS OF THE
RIVER HAVE NOT CHANGED MUCH

00:18:42.160 --> 00:18:45.530
SINCE TWAIN AND JAZBO'S
TIME BUT LIFE ON THE RIVER

00:18:45.530 --> 00:18:52.430
HAS CERTAINLY BEGUN
TO ALTER ITS COURSE.

00:18:52.430 --> 00:18:55.860
THIS USED TO BE A COMPLETELY
RURAL FARMING AREA RUN BY

00:18:55.860 --> 00:18:58.660
A FEW WEALTHY WHITE FAMILIES
WHO MADE THEIR FORTUNES

00:18:58.660 --> 00:19:02.130
BY GROWING COTTON
AND USING SLAVE LABOR.

00:19:02.130 --> 00:19:05.930
BUT IT'S NOW CHANGING WITH
BIG CORPORATE FARMS MOVING IN

00:19:05.930 --> 00:19:09.500
AND WITH STRIP MALLS, MOTELS,
AND BURGER BARS APPEARING

00:19:09.500 --> 00:19:13.960
WHERE THERE USED TO BE SHOTGUN
SHACKS AND JUKE JOINTS.

00:19:13.960 --> 00:19:16.860
UP UNTIL 10 YEARS AGO
TUNICA WAS JUST ABOUT

00:19:16.860 --> 00:19:19.030
THE POOREST TOWN
IN THE COUNTRY.

00:19:19.030 --> 00:19:22.560
IT USED TO BE CALLED AMERICA'S
ZIMBABWE BECAUSE OF ITS HARSH

00:19:22.560 --> 00:19:27.000
THIRD WORLD LIVING CONDITIONS
BUT NOW IT HAS HIT THE JACKPOT

00:19:27.000 --> 00:19:29.360
THANKS TO SOME OF THE
STRANGEST LOOKING BOATS

00:19:29.360 --> 00:19:35.100
EVER TO TAKE
TO THE RIVER.

00:19:35.100 --> 00:19:40.430
WHEN TENNESSEE LEGALIZED
GAMBLING IN THE 1990'S

00:19:40.430 --> 00:19:45.600
IT STATED THAT ALL ACTIVITY MUST
TAKE PLACE ON THE MISSISSIPPI

00:19:45.600 --> 00:19:48.730
AND SO TUNICA, LYING A FEW
MILES AWAY FROM THE RIVER,

00:19:48.730 --> 00:19:51.360
DIVERTED SOME OF
THE MISSISSIPPI'S FLOW

00:19:51.360 --> 00:19:54.230
TO CREATE SMALL POOLS
ON WHICH THEY COULD

00:19:54.230 --> 00:19:57.760
FLOAT THEIR MODERN DAY
PLEASURE PALACES.

00:19:57.760 --> 00:20:04.230
THEY DON'T LOOK LIKE BOATS AND
YOU CAN'T EVEN SEE THE WATER,

00:20:04.230 --> 00:20:07.960
BUT IT IS THERE, UNDERNEATH
ALL THE FLASHING LIGHTS AND

00:20:07.960 --> 00:20:11.100
SPINNING WHEELS AND IT'S
ALLOWED TUNICA TO BECOME

00:20:11.100 --> 00:20:15.030
THE THIRD LARGEST GAMING
REGION IN THE UNITED STATES.

00:20:15.030 --> 00:20:17.700
THE WORLD POKER CHAMPIONSHIP
HAS BEEN HELD HERE

00:20:17.700 --> 00:20:21.300
WITH $10,000 SET AS
THE MINIMUM BUY-IN.

00:20:21.300 --> 00:20:24.530
FORTUNES HAVE BEEN MADE AND
LOST BUT THE BIGGEST WINNER

00:20:24.530 --> 00:20:27.800
IS TUNICA ITSELF WITH THE
CASINOS NOW PROVIDING

00:20:27.800 --> 00:20:30.960
WORK FOR 10,000 PEOPLE
AND GENERATING ENOUGH

00:20:30.960 --> 00:20:33.830
TAX REVENUE TO
PROVIDE BETTER SCHOOLS,

00:20:33.830 --> 00:20:39.430
BETTER ROADS, AND A
BETTER QUALITY OF LIFE.

00:20:39.430 --> 00:20:47.130
WHAT EFFECT ALL THIS GLITZY
THEME PARKED WEALTH WILL HAVE

00:20:47.130 --> 00:20:49.500
ON THE CULTURE AND
MUSIC OF THE MISSISSIPPI,

00:20:49.500 --> 00:20:51.700
WE'LL HAVE TO
WAIT AND SEE.

00:20:51.700 --> 00:20:54.760
ONE THING IS CERTAIN... TUNICA'S
OVERNIGHT SUCCESS STORY

00:20:54.760 --> 00:21:00.060
SEEMS TO BE THE
EXCEPTION, NOT THE RULE.

00:21:00.060 --> 00:21:06.160
AS THE RIVER SEEPS DEEPER INTO
THE SOUTH AND INTO THE FAMOUS

00:21:06.160 --> 00:21:10.930
REGION KNOWN AS THE MISSISSIPPI
DELTA WHAT WE WILL SEE IS A

00:21:10.930 --> 00:21:14.600
PLACE THAT MAY NO LONGER BE
BOUND BY SLAVERY BUT IS STILL

00:21:14.600 --> 00:21:19.500
TODAY BOUND BY THE CHAINS
OF MODERN DAY POVERTY.

00:21:19.500 --> 00:21:23.000
WE'LL ALSO CATCH GLIMPSES
OF ITS COTTON RICH PAST,

00:21:23.000 --> 00:21:25.300
THE MANSIONS
AND VAST ESTATES

00:21:25.300 --> 00:21:31.130
AND SEE HOW THEY SIT NOW
IN THE 21ST CENTURY SOUTH.

