00:22:08.700 --> 00:22:11.530
THE DELTA WAS FORMED
OVER THOUSANDS OF YEARS

00:22:11.530 --> 00:22:13.800
AS THE MISSISSIPPI
FLOODED AND RECEDED

00:22:13.800 --> 00:22:16.230
LEAVING BEHIND IT A
RICH, SILTY DEPOSIT

00:22:16.230 --> 00:22:19.630
WHICH FORMED SOME OF
THE BEST SOIL IN THE WORLD.

00:22:19.630 --> 00:22:22.200
THIS GIFT OF THE MISSISSIPPI
ALLOWED THE DELTA

00:22:22.200 --> 00:22:24.800
TO DEVELOP INTO THE MOST
PRODUCTIVE AND RICHEST

00:22:24.800 --> 00:22:27.760
COTTON GROWING
CENTER IN AMERICA.

00:22:35.630 --> 00:22:39.160
THE DOLLAR WEALTH FROM THIS
LAND AND ITS COTTON PLANTATIONS

00:22:39.160 --> 00:22:42.600
WAS ALWAYS ENJOYED BY A
MINORITY OF LOCAL WHITE MASTERS

00:22:42.600 --> 00:22:44.900
BUT ITS RICH
CULTURAL HERITAGE

00:22:44.900 --> 00:22:47.900
FOUND ITS WAY TO THE
REST OF THE WORLD.

00:22:56.530 --> 00:22:59.860
RIGHT IN THE HEART OF
THE MISSISSIPPI DELTA

00:22:59.860 --> 00:23:02.400
LIES THE
HOBSON PLANTATION.

00:23:02.400 --> 00:23:04.600
IT'S STILL A WORKING FARM
WHICH HAS BEEN OWNED

00:23:04.600 --> 00:23:08.060
BY THE SAME FAMILY
FOR NEARLY 150 YEARS.

00:23:08.060 --> 00:23:11.300
BUT LIFE ISN'T EASY HERE
EVEN FOR THE ONCE WEALTHY

00:23:11.300 --> 00:23:13.930
WHITE POPULATION.

00:23:13.930 --> 00:23:16.400
EVER SINCE THE DEMAND
FOR COTTON DECREASED

00:23:16.400 --> 00:23:18.500
WITH CHEAPER CROPS BEING
PRODUCED ELSEWHERE

00:23:18.500 --> 00:23:21.030
IN THE WORLD, HOBSON'S
HAS HAD TO DIVERSIFY

00:23:21.030 --> 00:23:23.900
AND IS NOW A STRUGGLING
TOURIST ATTRACTION

00:23:23.900 --> 00:23:29.200
AS WELL AS A
STRUGGLING FARM.

00:23:29.200 --> 00:23:32.630
DAVID "HONEYBOY" EDWARDS
REMEMBERS THIS PLACE

00:23:32.630 --> 00:23:35.530
WHEN IT WAS A BUSY
PLANTATION, WITH HIS FAMILY

00:23:35.530 --> 00:23:42.200
ALONG WITH MANY OTHERS DOING
ALL THE COTTON PICKING WORK.

00:23:42.200 --> 00:23:46.530
AT 92, HONEYBOY IS THE
LAST LIVING DELTA BLUESMAN

00:23:46.530 --> 00:23:49.360
AND THE TRUE EMBODIMENT
OF THE MISSISSIPPI RIVER

00:23:49.360 --> 00:23:51.800
AND ITS CULTURE.

00:24:13.960 --> 00:24:16.900
HONEYBOY WAS PART OF A
SUBCULTURE OF BLUES ARTISTS

00:24:16.900 --> 00:24:19.430
WHO WERE REFUGEES FROM
THE PLANTATION SYSTEM.

00:24:19.430 --> 00:24:21.700
THESE MEN LIVED
ON THE WILD SIDE

00:24:21.700 --> 00:24:26.460
BUT THEIR SONGS CAME
OUT OF PAIN AND SUFFERING.

00:24:26.460 --> 00:24:29.060
IN THE BACK BREAKING,
HOT, SWELTERING DAYS

00:24:29.060 --> 00:24:31.560
THEY WOULD COMMUNICATE
WITH EACH OTHER BY CALLING

00:24:31.560 --> 00:24:34.600
AND ANSWERING IN
RHYME AND SONG.

00:25:14.630 --> 00:25:17.500
>>HONEYBOY GREW
UP WITH THE BLUES.

00:25:17.500 --> 00:25:20.700
HE WAS BORN IN THESE FIELDS,
THE GRANDSON OF A SLAVE

00:25:20.700 --> 00:25:24.130
AND THE SON OF
A SHARECROPPER.

00:25:24.130 --> 00:25:28.930
SHARECROPPING WAS
A TENANCY AGREEMENT

00:25:28.930 --> 00:25:31.830
WHICH ALLOWED FORMER
SLAVES TO RENT OUT

00:25:31.830 --> 00:25:34.660
A THIN STRIP OF LAND
AND WORK IT THEMSELVES,

00:25:34.660 --> 00:25:37.160
BUT IN EFFECT IT BOUND
THE BLACK WORKERS

00:25:37.160 --> 00:25:40.330
EVER MORE CLOSELY
TO THEIR MASTERS.

00:25:40.330 --> 00:25:42.530
THE SHARECROPPERS HAD
TO GIVE HALF THEIR CROP

00:25:42.530 --> 00:25:44.560
TO THE PLANTATION
OWNERS AND PAY BACK

00:25:44.560 --> 00:25:46.960
NEARLY ALL THEIR
PROFITS IN RENT.

00:25:46.960 --> 00:25:50.500
THEY ENDED UP OWING MONEY
AND SO WERE KEPT IN CHAINS

00:25:50.500 --> 00:25:54.060
AS EFFECTIVELY AS THEY
EVER HAD BEEN AS SLAVES.

00:26:17.700 --> 00:26:21.800
>>HONEYBOY KNEW HE
HAD TO GET OUT SOMEHOW

00:26:21.800 --> 00:26:25.560
AND SO ON HIS 17TH BIRTHDAY
HE PICKED UP HIS GUITAR,

00:26:25.560 --> 00:26:28.460
KISSED HIS MAMA ON
THE CHEEK, AND WENT OUT

00:26:28.460 --> 00:26:34.830
TO FOLLOW HIS DREAM
OF BECOMING A BLUESMAN.

00:26:34.830 --> 00:26:38.930
EVER SINCE SLAVES TRAVELED
UPSTREAM TO THE FREEDOM

00:26:38.930 --> 00:26:41.800
OF THE NORTH, AFRICAN
AMERICANS ALWAYS CHOSE TO

00:26:41.800 --> 00:26:44.930
FOLLOW THE RIVER ROUTE
WHENEVER THEY WENT TRAVELING.

00:26:44.930 --> 00:26:48.400
HONEYBOY DID THE SAME, KNOWING
THAT THE BLACK COMMUNITIES

00:26:48.400 --> 00:26:51.200
WHICH HAD SETTLED ALONG
THE BANKS OF THE MISSISSIPPI

00:26:51.200 --> 00:26:55.330
WOULD PROVIDE HIM WITH
A SAFE HAVEN AFTER DARK.

00:26:55.330 --> 00:27:05.430
♪

00:27:05.430 --> 00:27:12.200
♪

00:27:12.200 --> 00:27:15.130
TODAY, HONEYBOY IS STILL
TRAVELING UP AND DOWN

00:27:15.130 --> 00:27:18.060
THE MISSISSIPPI, PLAYING
HIS BLUES TO DELTA FOLK

00:27:18.060 --> 00:27:21.000
AND IS STILL ENJOYING HIS
ROCK AND ROLL LIFESTYLE

00:27:21.000 --> 00:27:24.560
WITH WOMEN
DANCING AT HIS FEET.

00:27:31.330 --> 00:27:34.760
COTTON IS STILL GROWN IN THESE
FIELDS BUT MOST OF THE FARMS

00:27:34.760 --> 00:27:37.100
ARE NOW RUN BY BIG
CORPORATE ORGANIZATIONS

00:27:37.100 --> 00:27:40.260
AND THE MANSIONS HAVE BEEN
BOUGHT UP BY RICH BUSINESSMEN

00:27:40.260 --> 00:27:44.000
WHO FANCIED A HOLIDAY
HOME IN THE SOUTH.

00:27:44.000 --> 00:27:48.530
MACHINES DO MOST OF THE
HARVESTING WORK WITH MANY

00:27:48.530 --> 00:27:52.460
DELTA DWELLERS HAVING TO MOVE
OUT TO FIND JOBS ELSEWHERE.

00:27:52.460 --> 00:27:55.230
FOR THOSE THAT REMAIN,
IT STILL SEEMS THAT

00:27:55.230 --> 00:27:57.760
IT'S THE AFRICAN AMERICANS
THAT DO THE HARD WORK

00:27:57.760 --> 00:28:02.300
WHILE WHITE
MANAGERS LOOK ON.

00:28:12.560 --> 00:28:15.160
OVER THE YEARS MANY PEOPLE
HAVE REAPED THE REWARDS

00:28:15.160 --> 00:28:17.100
THAT THE MISSISSIPPI
HAS BROUGHT -

00:28:17.100 --> 00:28:20.460
THE RICH SOIL, THE TRADE,
THE DIVERSE CULTURE.

00:28:20.460 --> 00:28:23.730
BUT ALL THIS IS JUST
PART OF THE STORY.

00:28:23.730 --> 00:28:26.300
THERE'S ALSO A VERY
DARK UNDERCURRENT

00:28:26.300 --> 00:28:29.660
THAT FLOWS THROUGH
THESE WATERS.

00:28:39.830 --> 00:28:42.560
THIS IS AN AWESOME
RIVER WHICH CAN CAUSE

00:28:42.560 --> 00:28:48.430
DEATH AND DESTRUCTION
ON A MASSIVE SCALE.

00:28:48.430 --> 00:28:52.300
WHEN HURRICANE KATRINA
HIT NEW ORLEANS IN 2005

00:28:52.300 --> 00:28:55.760
THE WORLD REALIZED THE
FULL EXTENT OF ITS FORCE.

00:28:55.760 --> 00:28:58.600
BUT IT WAS ONLY AFTER
THE WATERS HAD RECEDED

00:28:58.600 --> 00:29:03.300
THAT THE REAL TRUTH
FINALLY SURFACED.

00:29:03.300 --> 00:29:10.000
THE FLOOD WAS NOT JUST AN ACT OF
GOD, IT WAS A MAN-MADE DISASTER

00:29:10.000 --> 00:29:14.760
WHICH SHOULD
HAVE BEEN AVERTED.

00:29:14.760 --> 00:29:19.200
A SYSTEM OF LEVEES OSTENSIBLY
BUILT TO PROTECT THE POPULATION

00:29:19.200 --> 00:29:23.860
HAD ACTUALLY PUT THEM IN
THE GRAVEST OF DANGER.

00:29:23.860 --> 00:29:27.160
A LESSON WHICH SHOULD HAVE
BEEN LEARNED FROM THE PAST

00:29:27.160 --> 00:29:31.630
BECAUSE ALL THIS AND WORSE
HAD HAPPENED BEFORE.

00:29:38.260 --> 00:29:41.030
IN 1927, A MASSIVE
FLOOD ENGULFED

00:29:41.030 --> 00:29:43.400
THE WHOLE LOWER
MISSISSIPPI REGION

00:29:43.400 --> 00:29:47.400
WITH ITS EPICENTER IN THE LITTLE
DELTA TOWN OF GREENVILLE.

00:29:47.400 --> 00:29:51.430
FROM CAIRO TO NEW ORLEANS,
70,000 SQUARE KILOMETERS

00:29:51.430 --> 00:29:54.700
BECAME COVERED IN UP
TO 15 METERS OF WATER,

00:29:54.700 --> 00:29:58.260
WITH HUNDREDS OF THOUSANDS
OF PEOPLE LOSING THEIR HOMES,

00:29:58.260 --> 00:30:02.560
THEIR LAND,
AND THEIR LIVES.

00:30:02.560 --> 00:30:04.560
TWO OF THOSE WHO
SURVIVED THE FLOOD

00:30:04.560 --> 00:30:08.430
ARE KATHERINE
AND ELLIS SMITH.

00:30:08.430 --> 00:30:11.300
THE MISSISSIPPI
HAS NO PREJUDICE,

00:30:11.300 --> 00:30:16.100
IT DISPLACED AND KILLED
BLACK AND WHITE ALIKE.

00:30:29.960 --> 00:30:33.030
ELLIS AND HIS FAMILY WERE
POOR SUBSISTENCE FARMERS

00:30:33.030 --> 00:30:35.360
WHO HAD WORKED THIS
LAND FOR GENERATIONS.

00:30:35.360 --> 00:30:37.700
LIVING ON THE OUTSKIRTS OF
GREENVILLE RIGHT IN THE HEART

00:30:37.700 --> 00:30:41.600
OF THE DELTA, THEY WERE USED TO
THE FLOODS, GRATEFUL TO THEM,

00:30:41.600 --> 00:30:48.630
IN FACT, FOR IRRIGATING THEIR
CROPS AND RENEWING THEIR SOIL.

00:30:48.630 --> 00:30:51.860
BUT THAT FATEFUL
WINTER THE RAINS CAME

00:30:51.860 --> 00:30:54.400
IN BIBLICAL PROPORTIONS.

00:30:54.400 --> 00:30:57.660
THEY FELL FROM THE SKY
LIKE CRASHING WAVES

00:30:57.660 --> 00:31:01.630
BEATING DOWN ON
THOSE MOST VULNERABLE.

00:31:01.630 --> 00:31:04.160
THE RICH TOWNSFOLK
AND PLANTATION OWNERS

00:31:04.160 --> 00:31:06.960
HAD THE MEANS TO MOVE
AWAY TO HIGHER GROUND

00:31:06.960 --> 00:31:10.100
BUT THE POOR
WERE LEFT BEHIND

00:31:10.100 --> 00:31:14.360
AS THE RAIN FELL
AND THE RIVER ROSE.

00:32:10.730 --> 00:32:13.030
>>KATHERINE SMITH
LIVED ON HIGHER GROUND

00:32:13.030 --> 00:32:14.900
AWAY FROM
THE LEVEES.

00:32:14.900 --> 00:32:18.300
AS A YOUNG GIRL OF SIX, SHE
