00:46:25.000 --> 00:46:28.000
WITH MUSIC
AT ITS HEART.

00:46:28.000 --> 00:46:30.930
AFTER SUFFERING ONE OF THE
WORST NATURAL DISASTERS

00:46:30.930 --> 00:46:34.530
IN U.S. HISTORY, NEW ORLEANS IS
GAMELY GIVING THE IMPRESSION

00:46:34.530 --> 00:46:38.630
THAT THE GOOD TIMES
ARE ROLLING AGAIN.

00:46:38.630 --> 00:46:41.130
BUT A COUPLE OF MILES
TO THE NORTH OR EAST,

00:46:41.130 --> 00:46:43.960
THE CAJUN BRAVURA
AND THE VOODOO SPELLS

00:46:43.960 --> 00:46:46.830
FALL AWAY LIKE A
MARDI GRAS MASK,

00:46:46.830 --> 00:46:51.830
THE STREETS FALL QUIET AND
THE CITY BECOMES A DEAD ZONE.

00:47:07.600 --> 00:47:10.660
THIS IS THE NINTH WARD -
ONE OF THE LOWER LYING

00:47:10.660 --> 00:47:13.530
AND CONSEQUENTLY
POORER PARTS OF TOWN.

00:47:13.530 --> 00:47:18.400
MANY, PERHAPS MOST, OF THE
CITY'S DEAD CAME FROM HERE.

00:47:18.400 --> 00:47:20.960
AS WAS THE CASE IN
THE FLOOD OF 1927,

00:47:20.960 --> 00:47:24.500
THESE PEOPLE SIMPLY
HAD NO MEANS OF ESCAPE.

00:47:24.500 --> 00:47:27.600
THE BODIES WERE WASHED
AWAY WITH THE FLOOD WATERS

00:47:27.600 --> 00:47:31.460
OR LEFT TO ROT IN ATTICS,
WITH THE NUMBER OF DEAD

00:47:31.460 --> 00:47:34.760
LATER FOUND HERE EERILY
RECORDED IN BLACK PAINT

00:47:34.760 --> 00:47:41.630
ON THE CARCASSES
OF THEIR HOMES.

00:47:41.630 --> 00:47:44.430
THE MEMBERS OF THE NEW
WAVE JAZZ BAND WERE BORN

00:47:44.430 --> 00:47:46.830
AND BROUGHT
UP IN THE CITY.

00:47:46.830 --> 00:47:51.130
JULIUS LEWIS REMEMBERS
HOW THINGS USED TO BE.

00:47:51.130 --> 00:47:56.500
BEFORE KATRINA THIS PLACE
WAS ALIVE AND UP AND RUNNING.

00:47:56.500 --> 00:47:59.600
THERE WAS PEOPLE EVERYWHERE,
BUSINESSES BOOMING

00:47:59.600 --> 00:48:02.930
AND MOST PEOPLE DOWN
HERE OWNED THEIR HOUSES.

00:48:02.930 --> 00:48:06.630
THEY WERE SMALL
BUT MOSTLY OWNED.

00:48:06.630 --> 00:48:08.860
UNFORTUNATELY, THEY
DIDN'T HAVE INSURANCE

00:48:08.860 --> 00:48:12.630
BUT IT WAS VERY BUSY AND
VERY LIVELY, VERY SPIRITED.

00:48:12.630 --> 00:48:15.400
THEY HAD THEIR OWN TYPE
OF CULTURE DOWN HERE.

00:48:15.400 --> 00:48:19.560
IT'S SO SAD TODAY
TO SEE IT THIS WAY

00:48:19.560 --> 00:48:24.930
WITH NO HOUSES
AND NO PEOPLE.

00:48:24.930 --> 00:48:28.860
>>ON THE 29TH OF AUGUST,
2005, AS HURRICANE KATRINA

00:48:28.860 --> 00:48:32.930
PASSED TO THE EAST OF THE CITY,
THE FLOOD PROTECTION SYSTEM

00:48:32.930 --> 00:48:37.030
IN NEW ORLEANS FAILED
IN 53 DIFFERENT PLACES

00:48:37.030 --> 00:48:42.060
WITH NEARLY EVERY LEVEE IN
THE METRO AREA BREACHED.

00:48:42.060 --> 00:48:45.600
PERCY ELLICE SR. WAS
LUCKY ENOUGH TO OWN A CAR

00:48:45.600 --> 00:48:48.360
AND SO HE PILED IT HIGH WITH
AS MANY PEOPLE AS HE COULD

00:48:48.360 --> 00:48:50.830
AND RACED
OUT OF THE CITY.

00:48:50.830 --> 00:48:53.760
ONCE THE FLOOD HIT, I WENT OUT
TO THE COUNTRY AND TRIED NOT TO

00:48:53.760 --> 00:48:56.760
LOOK AT THE TELEVISION
BECAUSE IT WAS TOO DEPRESSING

00:48:56.760 --> 00:48:58.960
AND I KNEW EVENTUALLY I
WOULD HAVE TO COME BACK

00:48:58.960 --> 00:49:01.330
AND FACE THE REALITY
THAT EVERYTHING WAS GONE

00:49:01.330 --> 00:49:03.600
SO MY THOUGHTS WERE
BASICALLY ON REBUILDING

00:49:03.600 --> 00:49:07.230
MY LIFE FROM SCRATCH
AND MAKING IT MUCH BETTER.

00:49:07.230 --> 00:49:10.160
THE DISASTER PART, YOU
HAD TO PUT THAT BEHIND YOU

00:49:10.160 --> 00:49:12.900
AND MOVE FORWARD.
YOU CAN'T DWELL ON IT

00:49:12.900 --> 00:49:15.300
BECAUSE ALL THAT'LL DO
IS MAKE YOU DEPRESSED.

00:49:15.300 --> 00:49:17.860
YOU GOT TO PICK UP AND
START OVER AND SAY, HEY,

00:49:17.860 --> 00:49:20.660
GOD DOES EVERYTHING FOR
A REASON AND KEEP GOING.

00:49:20.660 --> 00:49:23.400
GO WITH THE FLOW.

00:49:23.400 --> 00:49:26.530
>>JULIUS HAD NO WAY OUT.
HE GOT TRAPPED IN THE CITY

00:49:26.530 --> 00:49:29.330
AND WAS LUCKY TO
ESCAPE WITH HIS LIFE...

00:49:29.330 --> 00:49:33.360
BUT HE LOST HIS HOME,
HIS FRIENDS AND HIS FAMILY.

00:49:33.360 --> 00:49:35.860
LIKE MOST OF NEW
ORLEANS' MUSICIANS,

00:49:35.860 --> 00:49:39.400
HE'S NOW RELOCATED IN ONE OF
THE OTHER TOWNS UPSTREAM

00:49:39.400 --> 00:49:44.630
BUT COMES BACK TO
PLAY WITH HIS BAND.

00:49:44.630 --> 00:49:48.830
TODAY, NEW ORLEANS IS
FIGHTING FOR ITS LIFE.

00:49:48.830 --> 00:49:51.700
THE FLOOD KILLED
NEARLY 2,000 PEOPLE

00:49:51.700 --> 00:49:54.260
AND WASHED
AWAY MANY MORE.

00:49:54.260 --> 00:49:57.760
ONLY HALF OF ITS POPULATION
AND ITS MUSICIANS RETURNED

00:49:57.760 --> 00:50:01.260
TO START REBUILDING
THEIR CITY AND THEIR LIVES.

00:50:01.260 --> 00:50:04.600
IT'S A STRUGGLE BUT LIKE MANY OF
THE OTHER PLACES WE'VE SEEN

00:50:04.600 --> 00:50:07.860
ALONG OUR JOURNEY, HOPE
LIVES ON HERE IN THE MINDS

00:50:07.860 --> 00:50:11.230
AND HEARTS OF THOSE WHO HAVE
SUFFERED AND LOST THE MOST

00:50:11.230 --> 00:50:15.200
AND IN THE MUSIC OF THE
YOUNGER GENERATION.

00:50:15.200 --> 00:50:18.260
THE BELIEF ON THE STREETS
IS THAT IF THE MUSIC SURVIVES

00:50:18.260 --> 00:50:21.860
THEN THE SPIRIT OF NEW
ORLEANS WILL LIVE ON.

00:50:21.860 --> 00:50:23.830
MUSIC IS NEW ORLEANS.

00:50:23.830 --> 00:50:26.230
WITHOUT MUSIC THERE'D
BE NO NEW ORLEANS.

00:50:26.230 --> 00:50:29.130
THE TRADITION, THE BRASS, THE
JAZZ, THE SOUND, THE FLOW...

00:50:29.130 --> 00:50:31.260
IT'S WHAT NEW
ORLEANS IS ALL ABOUT.

00:50:31.260 --> 00:50:33.260
THE TRADITION
MUST GO ON.

00:50:33.260 --> 00:50:35.530
YOU MUST PASS IT DOWN,
KEEP IT GOING, REGENERATE IT,

00:50:35.530 --> 00:50:37.630
KEEP THE ENERGY
AND THE FIRE GOING.

00:50:37.630 --> 00:50:39.130
THIS IS NEW ORLEANS.

00:50:39.130 --> 00:50:41.330
NEW ORLEANS IS JAZZ.
WHEN YOU THINK OF JAZZ,

00:50:41.330 --> 00:50:44.860
IT'S HERE THAT YOU'RE THINKING
ABOUT - NEW ORLEANS.

00:50:48.200 --> 00:50:50.730
>>AND SO AS WE COME TO
THE END OF OUR JOURNEY

00:50:50.730 --> 00:50:53.360
ALONG THE MISSISSIPPI AND
AS OL' MAN RIVER QUIETLY

00:50:53.360 --> 00:50:56.460
RETIRES TO THE SEA
WEARY FROM THE CENTURIES

00:50:56.460 --> 00:51:00.830
OF TRADE, TRAVEL, AND INJUSTICE
THAT HE HAS SEEN ALONG THE WAY,

00:51:00.830 --> 00:51:03.600
IT IS THE MUSIC AND
THE SPIRIT OF THE PLACE

00:51:03.600 --> 00:51:07.230
THAT WE TAKE WITH US; A
REMINDER THAT NO MATTER

00:51:07.230 --> 00:51:11.430
HOW HARD THE STRUGGLE OR
HOW HARSH THE CONDITIONS,

00:51:11.430 --> 00:51:14.700
THE TRUE SPIRIT OF
BOTH MAN AND THE RIVER

00:51:14.700 --> 00:51:18.700
JUST KEEPS
ROLLING ALONG.